name: Keto Pumpkin Bake
author: rocksoutforcheese
summary: A good keto breakfast, snack, or dessert! Store in fridge. Try it with a little Splenda®-sweetened whipped cream for a breakfast you will never get sick of!
ingredients: ½ cup granular sucrolose sweetener (such as Splenda®)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place cream cheese in a bowl; beat with an electric mixer until smooth
Add eggs and beat until well combined
Add pumpkin puree, sweetener, cinnamon, and pumpkin pie spice; mix well
Pour batter into an ungreased 8x8-inch baking pan
Bake in the preheated oven until center is set, about 45 minutes
Remove from oven and cool completely
